# Sentinel — Cursor Project Rules

`AGENTS.md` is the **canonical operating guide** and `PLAN.md` is the **full plan**.
Read both. This rule restates the non-negotiables and always applies.

## Project (one line)
**Sentinel** — an autonomous, risk-managed RWA yield vault on **Mantle** (chain ID
5000). An AI agent (Z.AI) allocates **USDC** across **USDY** (tokenized US
Treasuries), **Aave v3**, and **INIT**, rebalancing only within hard on-chain
guardrails and logging every decision on-chain under an **ERC-8004** identity.
Track: **AI × RWA**.

## Non-negotiables
- **1delta = data + optional swap routing ONLY.** Never in the custody/execution
  path. The vault must never execute arbitrary third-party calldata. Execution
  happens only via our own adapters (`AaveV3Adapter`, `UsdyAdapter`, `InitAdapter`)
  that call protocols directly with on-chain `minOut`/guardrail checks.
- **Guardrails are final.** LLM proposes → deterministic validator checks against
  guardrails → immutable on-chain guardrails are the backstop. The model is never
  the last line of defense. Guardrails: max weight/strategy, min idle buffer, max
  slippage, token/strategy whitelist, rebalance-frequency cap, per-tx caps,
  pause/kill switch, add-strategy timelock.
- **AI only where it beats an algorithm.** Keep yield/optimization/peg/utilization/
  execution deterministic. Use the LLM only for: unstructured→structured risk
  signals, written rationale, novel-event judgment, conversational UX. No AI-washing.
- **Mantle-only** (chain ID 5000). No other execution chains. Solana/Byreal is out.
- **Custody safety.** USDC is the only deposit asset. USDY is sourced via **DEX,
  blocklist-aware**, never KYC-gated mint in the vault path. ALLOCATOR is a
  guardrail-bounded hot key with a kill switch.
- **Verify before integrating.** Treat addresses in `PLAN.md` as unverified until
  confirmed on-chain. Develop/test against `anvil --fork` of Mantle mainnet first.
- **Ground-truth reads via RPC** for held assets (Aave position, USDY); 1delta is
  breadth/UX only.
- **Never commit secrets.** Git-ignored `.env` + documented `.env.example`. No
  secret logging.
- **Scope discipline (MoSCoW):** Must → Should → Could. Feature-freeze **2026-06-12**.

## Stack (do not substitute without asking)
Solidity + Foundry (forge/anvil/cast) · React + Vite + Tailwind + daisyUI · Node.js
+ TypeScript + Fastify · Vitest + Forge tests · Docker + Caddy/nginx · Z.AI · 1delta
API + Mantle RPC.

## Conventions
- TypeScript strict; no plain JS source. Solidity: explicit visibility, custom
  errors, NatSpec, checks-effects-interactions, reentrancy guards on fund-moving
  functions, prefer OpenZeppelin/Solmate.
- Comments explain non-obvious intent only; never narrate code or "explain the change."
- Every fund-moving contract needs Forge fork tests (happy path + guardrail
  violation + liquidity-crunch withdrawal). Risk engine + validator need Vitest.

## Workflow
Branches `cursor/<descriptive-name>-46a8` (lowercase); one logical change per
commit; draft PRs via the PR tool. Keep `PLAN.md` / `AGENTS.md` / `CLAUDE.md` / this
rule in sync. When unsure about guardrails, custody, the 1delta boundary, or scope —
**ask first.**
